value.0: This rather overweight Tainted shuffles through his shop, odd bits of food stuck into his scales.  He gives you a condescending glance, "What is it that you want?"

With a suddenly focused look, the Tainted says, "Be warned.  Changing the game default rules may lead to some unexpected results.  By changing the default rules, you agree to not hold the management, namely myself, responsible for any damage incurred."

"Which rules would you like to change?"

* Current Defaults*

<CUSTOM670>
"Sorry.  I don't sample the merchandise myself.  Try some of the players in the back."
With a bored sigh, he responds, "We sell Creature starter decks, expansion packs, and a few of the more common cards individually."
He gestures towards his display with a bored look.
"Very well, he sighs.  That will be 50 gold pieces.  You'll get five new cards added to your deck."
He hands over the expansion pack, which glitters magically and merges with your deck.
"Just look in your card bag.  When your bag fills up, you'll find it with the rest of your scattered inventory. "
"The price of the expansion decks aren't set by me.  I'm sure it's a conspiracy, but they still come back to buy them.  Now, want one or not?"
He looks at you closely.  "You don't appear to have a starter deck.  You'll need one of those first."

The owner looks like he's said this a thousand times.  "By purchasing this Creature deck, you acknowledge that this store assumes no liability for extreme addictive behavior including, but not limited to, pulling out hair, lack of sleep, clawing out eyes, or other self-destructive actions."
"You will also be given a bag to store any loose cards you may obtain.  It also records your score when you compete.  As a security precaution, you will be unable to drop this card bag."
"Very well.  That will be 10 gold pieces."  He holds out his scaly hand.
"Thank-you-for-your-business," he mutters in a single breath, pocketing the gold and handing you a fresh Creatures deck.
